Awesome selection of whiskeys/whiskys and food to pair. Try one of their game burgers. I took Jake's recommendation and tried the veal burger. Couldn't have made a better choice. Since it got a little chilly walking to the restaurant, I felt like having a peaty whisky. I paired my meal with a Bruichladdich Octomore 7.1. God, it was so smooth. Like drinking silky smooth honey with Huge smoke. I ordered ribs to go. It came packed with utensils, napkins, wet wipes, 3 different BBQ sauces, and my 2 sides (cornbread and coleslaw). Needless to say that I devoured everything like a savage animal. A place to surely swing by during my next trip out to St Louis.  If you're dying to try some exquisite whiskeys, their top shelf includes Pappy and Yamazaki 18, both very rare and hard to find.

Saw the $15 bottomless Mimosa sign so I decided to investigate.... Coming here for Sunday brunch was very refreshing. Best bloody Mary I’ve ever had, bottomless mimosas weren’t made with that cheap champagne that tastes like vomit, the bartender/server was very friendly, service was fast, and he even noticed that we had a small portion of potatoes, said “that looks light” and had the kitchen make us some more! We were one of two tables in the entire restaurant, so the atmosphere was great with it not being packed like every other brunch place. Would recommend for brunch!

If you want barbecue go to bandannas they treat you like family and their food is delicious.

I love this place. the wood design is warm and welcoming - gives a real "western saloon" style. The food is very good and I'm dying to try their smoked variety of meat. Now... the alcohol is fabulous. huge selection of bourbon and whiskey, cocktails are very well made. I love the old fashioned here! the people working here and the owner just love the place and love to serve their customers.

Decided to try the BBQ Saloon for dinner. After seeing the place packed all the time I thought it must be good. It was slow for a Monday night which does not bother me, but the drink options are scarce if you aren't a whiskey drinker.  We ordered the pulled pork nachos as a starter and were very regretful of that decision once it was brought to the table. It was tortilla chips, melted cheese, and pulled pork you can buy at the grocery store to be reheated at home......not only did it taste bad, it looked disgusting. They advertise it as nachos with the works, but there was nothing else on them.  I ordered the pulled pork sandwich before seeing the nachos, and was necous for it to be brought out. I also ordered green beans and Cole slaw. The pulled pork I got was completely different from what came on the nachos. It was bland and ok. My green beans were undercooked and bad, and the Cole slaw is bland. Overall, wasn't impressed with my choice.  My boyfriend ordered the ribs, which where dry and bland as well. He had Mac n cheese and fries as a side. Mac n cheese was good and the fries were Wendy's quality. He wasn't impressed either.  Overall, neither of us finished our dinner or took home the left over. Service was slow for us being the only ones there ordering food. My boyfriend loves whiskey so the only reason we will be going back is for him to drink. I'd go somewhere else to eat.

I was in St. Louis for my husband's open heart surgery and this place was so nice and so good I visited 3 times while I was in town. They have wonderful daily specials, a delicious brunch and great happy hour deals. I had shaved beef in my first visit, Shaved beef Benedict my second visit and two ribs and the shot special for happy hour. The beef in both beef dishes was very tender, the sauces are great. The two ribs were delicious as was the shot special which was a lemon drop. In my first two visits the wait staff was the same and they recognized me, even waved and said hi once when I was just walking past the place on the street. They are also a whiskey bar and their selection is extensive. The display is beautiful and I regret that I do not like whiskey. They also offer a short list of other cocktails which I ordered from and the drink was delicious. Over all I highly recommend this place. If I lived in town I would probably be a regular.

Decent food. The candy bacon was too sweet and cold. The ribs were too fatty, under seasoned, but tender. The pulled chicken sandwich was bland. Consider using salt before cooking, this will take ordinary to extraordinary. The service although quick, was not the friendliest, felt rushed as though we were in the way. Slow down and acknowledge customers as people. Busy is no excuse for borderline rudeness.

We were doing our best to keep her quiet even though there were only three other people in the entire building on the opposite side of the wall by the bar. A man came around the wall and said “Your baby is disturbing the people in the bar.” At first we thought he was joking. (He was not!) Come to find out from our waitress (who did a great job) that he was the owner!   Not only do we not recommend the subpar bbq, but also don’t recommend patronizing a place where the owner is so out of touch with reality and also does not appreciate his customers. (And, probably why his bar was basically empty.) We should have let our raging 5 year old “punch him in the neck” as he suggested he do.

Solely basing this review on food.  Had to check out this place after all these raving reviews... and couldn't have been more disappointed. I got the BBQ chicken, and it was the driest thing I have ever eating. I had to load it with BBQ sauce (house made) to get it down. The corn bread (one of my favorite foods), was dry as well (tasted like cornbread and nothing special). The place is NOT cheap at all, so I had to ensure I ate my full $15 dried out chicken meal. Very disappointed and won't be back as there are a few other BBQ spots (in St. Louis) that are head and shoulders above this place.  Nice atmosphere though..

One of the lesser known barbecue places in St. Louis.  Not cheap but good food with large portions.  Excellent ribs and pulled pork. The surprise is the smoked turkey and the garlic green beans.  If you are whiskey fan it is hard to find a bigger selection with 2 oz. pours standard.  Again, not the cheapest place to drink but fair prices for both whiskey and food.  We often get the sample for $38 and split it.  Our other option is a full rack of ribs for $26, which we also split.

Food was incredible. The amount of food/food portion to price ratio is really good. Staff were also very nice and helpful in informing us of the items on the menu. Would definitely recommend this place.

I can not say enough great things about this place!!!! Delicious food.  I love the atmosphere and energy. Excellent libations!!!! And Phil is a breath of fresh air and is happy to educate you if you're whiskey neophyte.
Great food and atmosphere.  Owner was a lot of fun.
Very good service great food the BBQ was delicious

A 💎! If a place executed either their rib smoker OR their whiskey menu as well as BBQ Saloon, they'd be worth a special trip. To execute both so well is astounding. They boast a menu of over 500 world whiskeys, from approachable to esoteric. Yet still make incredible happy hour specials like an old fashioned for $5. The ribs are among the best in St Louis and the mac n cheese is some of the best I've ever had. It's served like an ice cream, with cheese just dropping all over the top.
No mimosas, cheese missing on one of the meals. Over priced drinks. The smoked turkey was good so there's that.
The greatest whisky collection in the mid west indeed!  Delicious ribs, super friendly service. A true Midwest experience!

I've lived in St. Louis almost my entire life and I have never had soul food as good as this place. The Mac N cheese defy was hands down amazing, he could give my grandma tips on it... Leon Crues is the chef and makes the place what it is. He greeted us at the table answered all of our questions and cleared our dishes. It was like being at my Aunt and Uncle's after church having Sunday lunch. The outdoor seating with the string lights gives the feel of being at a backyard BBQ, while everyone kids and adults alike play games and have a good time. If you're looking for a taste of true St. Louis BBQ/soul food come here!! You can't describe how good the food is in words, you simply have to taste it.
Beef ribs are nuts. Whiskey collection is insane.
Good bbq with an interesting drink menu.
meh - service was poor and the food worse.

Had the bison this time, excellent! !! Our waitress more than excellent. Nice to be recognized by her after just a few visits over several months time. Will be back when we can.

We had a group of 31 attend tonight. After 6 people ordered, they ran out of pork ribs. After 10 more people, they ran out of beef ribs.  These are their two specialties.   We told them we were coming weeks in advance.   They were woefully understaffed.  It took almost 2 hours for everyone to be served food. A big mistake attending this restaurant.

My dad wanted beef ribs...I Googled and BBQ Saloon came up. He loved them and so did I...and I don't eat much beef anymore but I just had to try them.  The chicken was tender, the mac and cheese was off the chain!!

This place is incredible. Food was excellent and people are right about the candy bacon, it was as delicious as people say. The bourbon selection is insane, bourbon for days. The part that stands out the most is the staff, they were great. We are already planning our next visit.
Used to be better. Lazy with cocktail making. Food is alright, but don't expect top quality STL barbecue.

This location is a whiskey bar that serves good food.  The food was really good. Our group ordered the ribs and the pulled pork plate. The ribs came right off the bone and the pulled pork was tender but not undercooked. The prices were on the the high side but not unreasonable.  The drink selection seemed phenomenal. Great selection of whiskey both from local distilleries and abroad. The beer selection was decent with a good mix of local brews.  I would go back in heart beat! I recommend this place!
